PURPOSE: This hook is executed after the standard write, edits have been applied to the data., , Active Variables:,  WRITE.DATA,  ERROR.OCCURRED,  WARNING.OCCURRED,  MSG,  MSG.ARGUMENTS

FMT string used on write, , The format syntax is as follows:, , length{f.char}[L,R,T,C]{n}{$}{,}{Z}{mask}, , lenght and either L, R, T, or C are required.  All others, are optional., , length - total number of characters to appear in the,     output string, f.char - character used to fill the formatted string;,     default is space; since this follows length,,     and both might be numeric, f.char can be,     prefixed with a backslash (\) to indicate that,     it is the fill character and not part of the length, L      - left justify, R - right justify, C      - center the text, T      - text justification, n      - max number of decimal places allowed (numeric data only), $      - put $ at head of string (numeric data only), , - separate thousands by comas (numeric data only), Z      - zero suppress (value of zero becomes null), mask   - pattern mask, , Examples:, , SSN = 123456789, If this field is 11L###-##-####, SSN becomes 123-45-6789, , X = 816526, If this field is 12R2$, X becomes    $8,165.26, (3 leading spaces since it's right justified), , X = 44, If this field is 4\0R, X becomes 0044, , This means this field can be used to right justify and zero, fill data., , See the FMT UniBasic function for more info.

This is the institution with which this school is associated. This is, used for places that have one Colleague database, but need to report, multiple FICE codes., , This does NOT imply that this release of Colleague is a multi-, institution system. This simply allows a consortium of multiple FICE, codes to list the FICE (or any other) code from the INSTITUTIONS file, on reports., , If your institution has departments or divisions associated to, schools, the institution ID can be entered for schools instead of for, divisions or departments. Colleague looks at departments first, since, most transactions in the Colleague applications other than Core can, be traced back to a department. If no institution exists for the, department, then Colleague checks if a division or school is, associated with the department. If so, it checks the division or, school for an institution ID. If a division was being checked, and, there is no institution for the division, but the division is, associated to a school, then the school is checked for an institution, ID. If no institution ID is found anywhere, the ID entered on the, PID2 (ID and LookUp Parameters) screen in the Host Organization ID, field is used.

It is generated when EDX calls DMI to send a, transaction and the transaction is successfully sent., , This field is system-maintained and not meant to be, modified by users.

The date on which SEVIS should get the transaction.  This, is needed to know when a GET request can be sent since SEVIS, will not automatically send back results, and the transactions, sent are processed overnight.  Any transactions received prior, to 11:59 p.m. are processed starting at midnight.  Any, transactions sent after 11:59 p.m., or that are sent between, 11:59 p.m. on Saturday and 6 a.m. on Monday are processed, the following evening.  This means if DMI gets the transaction, prior to 11:59 Monday through Saturday, this field will be set, to the day DMI sent the transaction; after 11:59 p.m. or on, Sunday, this will be set to the following day.

If this is a dependent transaction, then this is the, ID of the dependent affected by the transaction., , Note that although a create student or exchange visitor, transaction can create dependents, those are NOT in, this field; this is strictly for when a dependent is, affected on an existing student or exchange visitor.
The code of the error that was returned from SEVIS.
This is the text of the error message returned from, SEVIS.

The date the most recent GET request was issued.  As, long as the status (SEVSTAT.STATUS) stays at G,, Clients can choose to resend the GET request., A successful GET will update the status, to either an E[rror], with an error message in, SEVSTAT.ERROR.MESSAGE, or U[pdated], meaning a SEVIS ID, and/or a .PDF has been added to the Colleague database.
This is either a school code or a program number; if, SEVSTAT.PERSON.TYPE = "S", it's a school code and if, SEVSTAT.PERSON.TYPE = "E" it's a program number.

This is the Colleague ID of the designated school, official (DSO) of a student or the responsible officer, (RO) of an exchange visitor.  This is used to allow, limiting the number of records shown to a selected, DSO or RO (see STS014).
Pointer to principal PERSON affected by transaction.  This, would be the ID of the nonimmigrant student or exchange, visitor, not a dependent.
The type of person being dealt with from a visa point, of view.  If this is S, the person is a student with, an F-1 or M-1 visa.  If this is E, the person is an, exchange visitor with a J-1 visa.
The time the transaction was sent to DMI for delivery to SEVIS.
This is the current status of the XML document.  It is, set by Colleague based on the state of the transaction.
The name of the XML document for this transaction.
